xwntv3GD1dudqDEOR7OZmp35XNo3CK2yetyUybbbozIga-mRq2HIzlkhUcoFErYMJDGJFPpilfe5UIZNi_7FOtZfFqbD2GDHZmmAHvPBm7GlNR97kj66A9DEkfJXOL6lrqEnKX-uogsa0bd9DGNrcUtd1HAKIoT9N3BnZTNwZPBCI-7xRe7RrEhm_dDIritPQZAsy1YPmh9WjH8amiJvlz3KQz21Xa4ux4zESeFkkoGL15DFta-4fPCK09CdvyJGg4d5ruSclPYQhErgYMOURpxpCL4aQzTi_JBtaNLmr-ULb8myq7AV-kKt-EIsez0rZx2n-m4EVTH73AeyWeIZD0WXbvR9PGz8mKV-3NIqoOjw-TUPOIc18dv-TVkUWrZm-EtLvvqXZhVeTaG8C1F76XoDfBzVTtfqaRpHis9UJnqNpb9Qpcd4KoYZEKtvvr76_UXGMV6xaYVfB4m3aDsz2Xsud7ixO5rztv\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering coverage logic**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out why the system isn't recognizing line numbers. Maybe if there are no line numbers, the coverage system can only account for methods where the call site line is unknown, but I don’t think it works that way. I'm wondering if there's a way to update the build logic for this. However, it seems unrelated to what I’m really trying to accomplish here. It feels like I should focus on changing tests until the harness catches on.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating serialization methods**\\n\\nI'm considering using `BCDHPrivateKey` in the serialization method, but I'm not sure if it will clarify the report. It seems better to edit the code to specifically reference `BCDHPrivateKey`, as it asserts the original class. However, I wonder if both `getEncoded` methods should be called? Then there's a potential issue: is `BCDHPrivateKey` serializable? Since it implements a series of interfaces that extend Serializable, I should be okay—just need to check test results. I might add a line to assert that `serializedKey` is not empty, too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_C6ULYaj1eb2uSdJwIoG3khHK|fc_02d53e5c2b6a4a77016a25af37960c8193a0aa14c2601f3a4d", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/BCDHPrivateKeyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import javax.crypto.interfaces.DHPrivateKey;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n", "newText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n"}, {"oldText": "        DHPrivateKey originalKey = createPrivateKey();\n\n        byte[] encodedKey = serialize(originalKey);\n        Object restoredKey = deserialize(encodedKey);\n\n        assertThat(restoredKey).isInstanceOf(BCDHPrivateKey.class);\n        DHPrivateKey restoredPrivateKey = (DHPrivateKey) restoredKey;\n        assertThat(restoredPrivateKey.getX()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getX());\n        assertThat(restoredPrivateKey.getParams().getP()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getParams().getP());\n        assertThat(restoredPrivateKey.getParams().getG()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getParams().getG());\n        assertThat(restoredPrivateKey.getParams().getL()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getParams().getL());\n    }\n\n    private static DHPrivateKey createPrivateKey() throws Exception {\n", "newText": "        BCDHPrivateKey originalKey = createPrivateKey();\n\n        byte[] serializedKey = serialize(originalKey);\n        BCDHPrivateKey restoredKey = deserialize(serializedKey);\n\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getX()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getX());\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getParams().getP()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getParams().getP());\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getParams().getG()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getParams().getG());\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getParams().getL()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getParams().getL());\n    }\n\n    private static BCDHPrivateKey createPrivateKey() throws Exception {\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static byte[] serialize(DHPrivateKey privateKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream output = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\n            output.writeObject(privateKey);\n        }\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static Object deserialize(byte[] serializedKey) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream input = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(serializedKey))) {\n            return input.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static byte[] serialize(BCDHPrivateKey privateKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream output = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\n            output.writeObject(privateKey);\n        }\n        assertThat(bytes.size()).isGreaterThan(0);\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static BCDHPrivateKey deserialize(byte[] serializedKey) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream input = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(serializedKey))) {\n            return (BCDHPrivateKey) input.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n"}]}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/BCDHPrivateKeyTest.java\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"import javax.crypto.interfaces.DHPrivateKey;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\",\"newText\":\"import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"        DHPrivateKey originalKey = createPrivateKey();\\n\\n        byte[] encodedKey = serialize(originalKey);\\n        Object restoredKey = deserialize(encodedKey);\\n\\n        assertThat(restoredKey).isInstanceOf(BCDHPrivateKey.class);\\n        DHPrivateKey restoredPrivateKey = (DHPrivateKey) restoredKey;\\n        assertThat(restoredPrivateKey.getX()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getX());\\n        assertThat(restoredPrivateKey.getParams().getP()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getParams().getP());\\n        assertThat(restoredPrivateKey.getParams().getG()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getParams().getG());\\n        assertThat(restoredPrivateKey.getParams().getL()).isEqualTo(originalKey.getParams().getL());\\n    }\\n\\n    private static DHPrivateKey createPrivateKey() throws Exception {\\n\",\"newText\":\" 